## 1. Project Overview
 
**SG Explorer** is a curated "things to do in Singapore" web app targeting people in their late 20s. It lists activities, upcoming events, and weekend trip destinations, and is **automatically updated every Monday and Wednesday** by an AI agent (Claude Cowork scheduled task) that adds new content to the data file and pushes it to GitHub.
 
- **Live site:** https://sg-explorer.vercel.app
- **GitHub repo:** https://github.com/njmvm/sg-explorer
- **Local path (Windows):** `C:\Users\mouge\sg-explorer\`
- **Deployment:** Vercel — auto-deploys on every push to `main`
- **Framework:** Next.js 14 App Router, JavaScript (not TypeScript)
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS (utility classes only — no custom config beyond what's in `tailwind.config.js`)
- **Images:** Unsplash (no account needed, direct photo URLs)
- **Map:** Leaflet.js + OpenStreetMap tiles (loaded from CDN, no API key needed)
 
