## 3. The Data File — `data/content.js` (CRITICAL)
 
This is the most important file in the project. **The automated AI agent reads and writes only this file.** It exports five named constants:
 
```js
export const categories   // filter categories — do NOT rename or reorder
export const badgeColors  // category → Tailwind class map — do NOT modify
export const activities   // array of activity objects
export const events       // array of event objects
export const trips        // array of trip objects
```
 
### 3a. Activity Object Schema
 
Every activity object **must** include all these fields (the AI agent writes them all):
 
```js
{
  id: 'karting',                     // unique kebab-case string
  slug: 'go-karting-kf1',            // URL-friendly slug
  category: 'sports',                // see categories list below
  title: 'Go-Karting at KF1',
  shortDesc: 'One sentence shown on the card.',
  fullDesc: 'Two to three sentences shown in the modal.',
  image: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-XXXXXXXXX?w=800&h=500&fit=crop&q=80',
  location: 'Buona Vista, Singapore',
  duration: '~2 hours',
  price: '~S$35/session',
  tags: ['Friends', 'Birthday', 'Competitive'],
  lat: 1.3068,       // Singapore latitude (always between 1.20–1.47)
  lng: 103.7912,     // Singapore longitude (always between 103.60–104.00)
  website: 'https://www.kf1.com.sg',  // official website URL
}
```
 
### 3b. Event Object Schema
 
```js
{
  id: 'e1',
  category: 'nightlife',
  title: 'Zouk \u2014 Techno Night',          // use \u2014 for em dash
  location: 'Zouk Singapore, Clarke Quay',
  time: '10 PM \u2013 late',                  // use \u2013 for en dash
  date: {
    month: 'APR',       // 3-letter uppercase month abbreviation
    day: '25',          // day number as string, OR 'SAT' for recurring
    label: 'Sat 25 Apr 2026',  // human-readable, ALWAYS include 4-digit year
  },
  tab: 'week',          // 'week' | 'month' | 'recurring'
  price: '~S$30',
  image: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-XXXXXXXXX?w=800&h=500&fit=crop&q=80',
  fullDesc: 'Two to three sentences.',
  tags: ['Clubbing', 'Techno'],
  lat: 1.2887,
  lng: 103.8467,
  website: 'https://www.zoukclub.com',
}
```
 
For **recurring events**, use:
```js
date: { month: 'EVERY', day: 'SAT', label: 'Every Saturday' },
tab: 'recurring',
```
 
### 3c. Trip Object Schema
 
```js
{
  id: 'batam',
  name: 'Batam, Indonesia',
  meta: 'Golf \u00B7 Spas \u00B7 Seafood',    // \u00B7 = middle dot separator
  transport: '\uD83D\uDEA4 1h ferry',           // MUST contain 'ferry', 'drive', or 'flight'
  image: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-XXXXXXXXX?w=800&h=600&fit=crop&q=80',
  vibe: 'One evocative sentence.',
  description: 'Two sentences of context.',
  gettingThere: 'How to reach from Singapore.',
  thingsToDo: [
    'Nagoya Hill \u2014 bargain shopping',      // \u2014 = em dash
    'Seafood at Golden Prawn \u2014 amazing',
  ],
  lat: 1.0456,       // destination coordinates (NOT Singapore)
  lng: 104.0305,
  website: 'https://www.batamfast.com',
}
```
 
### 3d. Valid Categories
 
```
sports | nightlife | food | nature | culture | social | travel
```
 
The `travel` category is used for weekend trips filter only. Activities and events use the other six.
 
