## 5. Component Reference
 
### `MapView.js`
- **Props:** `items` (array of activity/event/trip objects with `lat`/`lng`), `center` (optional `[lat, lng]`), `zoom` (default 12), `regional` (boolean, default false)
- **Behavior:** Loads Leaflet from CDN (`unpkg.com/leaflet@1.9.4`), renders a small map (200px), expands to 460px via "Expand map" button
- **Color coding:** Each category has a fixed dot color (blue=sports, purple=nightlife, amber=food, etc.)
- **Important:** Uses `scrollWheelZoom: false` to prevent scroll hijacking
- **SSR safe:** Uses `useEffect` for all Leaflet initialization — never calls `window.L` during SSR
 
### `CalendarView.js`
- **Props:** `events` (array), `onEventClick` (callback with event object)
- **Behavior:** Month calendar with prev/next navigation. Recurring events appear on every matching weekday. Clicking an event chip calls `onEventClick`.
- **Date matching:** Uses `MONTH_MAP` for `date.month` → 0-indexed month, and `DAY_MAP` for recurring day names
 
### `ActivityModal.js` / `EventModal.js` / `TripModal.js`
- All are client components with `open` + `onClose` props
- Show `website` link as primary CTA button ("Official website →" / "Event website →" / "Plan this trip →")
- ActivityModal shows a Google Maps directions link
- EventModal shows Google Calendar + Apple Calendar (.ics) export
- Close button uses `\u2715` (✕), Save button uses `\u2661` (♡)
 
### `EventRow.js`
- Shows event in list format with date box, title, location, time
- Has inline Google Calendar + Apple Calendar buttons (no modal needed to add to calendar)
 
