## 6. The Automated Update System
 
An AI agent (Claude Cowork scheduled task) runs **every Monday and Wednesday at 9 AM** and:
 
1. Reads `data/content.js` using PowerShell `Get-Content`
2. Adds 2–3 new activities, 3–5 new events, and optionally 1 new trip
3. Writes the updated file back using Desktop Commander
4. Runs `git add data/content.js && git commit && git push origin main`
5. Vercel auto-deploys within ~1 minute
 
**What the agent depends on (DO NOT break these contracts):**
 
- The five named exports from `data/content.js` must keep their exact names: `categories`, `badgeColors`, `activities`, `events`, `trips`
- The `tab` field on events must be exactly `'week'`, `'month'`, or `'recurring'` — the events page filter uses this
- The `transport` field on trips must contain the exact word `'ferry'`, `'drive'`, or `'flight'` — the trips page uses `.includes()` to filter into sections
- The `lat` and `lng` fields must be present on all items for the map to show markers
- The `website` field must be present for the modal CTA button to appear
- The file must remain pure ASCII — no raw emoji, only `\uXXXX` escapes
 
